modules.description: This module provides operations for mapping, filtering, and folding over lazy sequences, along with combinatorial constructs like product generation, interleaving, and subset enumeration. It works with finite sequences derived from lists, sets, ranges, or bitsets, supporting transformations and queries while preserving laziness for memory efficiency. Typical applications include processing large datasets without full materialization, generating structured combinations, and implementing algorithms requiring controlled enumeration of nested or variable-length data.

This library provides arithmetic and bitwise operations on 64-bit integers, including signed/unsigned division, shifts, and bit-level manipulations, alongside utilities like absolute value and successor functions. It supports conversions to and from numeric types (int, float, int32), string parsing, IEEE 754 bit transformations
